               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Sinodos (fols. 2ra-105vb), incomplete 
 I-1) Statutes or
                     Commandments (tǝʾǝzazat) of the Apostles (fols. 2ra-2vb, 6ra-11vb, 18ra-18vb,
                     20ra-26vb, 54ra-54vb, 76ra-80vb, 82ra-82vb, 105ra-105vb), incomplete 
 I-2)
                     Canons of the Council of Nicaea (20) (fols. 3ra-3vb, 12ra-12vb, 14ra-14va
                     [explicit]), incomplete 
 I-3) Canons of the Council of Nicaea (84) (fols.
                     4ra-4vb, 13ra-rb, 14va [incipit]-17vb, 27ra-28rb [explicit], 29ra-34vb),
                     incomplete
 I-4) Exposition and admonition to believers on wise conduct
                     (fols. 5ra-5vb, 57va [incipit]-63vb, 99ra-100vb), incomplete
 I-5) Epistle
                     70 by Cyprian of Carthage (fols. 28rb [incipit]-28vb, 81ra-81va
                     [explicit])
 I-6) Canons of the Council of Laodicea (fols. 35ra-37vb,
                     41ra-42vb [explicit], 97ra [incipit]-98vb)
 I-7) Discourse of the 318
                     Nicene Fathers on the Right Faith and on the Monastic Life (fols. 38ra-38rb
                     [explicit], 81vb [incipit], 89ra-90rb)
 I-8) Canons of the Council of
                     Gangra (fols. 38va [incipit]-40rb [explicit])
 I-9) Canons of the Council
                     of Sardica (fols. 40rb [incipit]-40vb, 91ra-92vb [explicit])
 I-10)
                     Interpretation of the Ten Commandments by John Chrysostom (fols. 42va
                     [incipit]-49va [explicit])
 I-11) Exposition and admonition on the role of
                     Our Lord in our salvation (also called On the Essence of the Holy Trinity)
                     (fols. 49va [incipit]-51rb [explicit])
 I-12) Exposition and admonition on
                     the way of virtue and perdition (also called How to Distinguish between God and
                     Evil) (fols. 51rb [incipit]-52ra [explicit])
 I-13) Exposition and
                     admonition on the fear of God (fols. 52rb [incipit]-53vb, 65ra-65va [explicit],
                     83ra-83vb), incomplete
 I-14) Exposition and admonition of Gregory of
                     Armenia against the Jews (fols. 56ra-57va [explicit], 73rb [incipit]-75vb)
                     I-15) Exposition and admonition to Believers on Wise Conduct (fols. 57va
                     [incipit]-63vb, 99ra-101vb [explicit]), incomplete
 I-16) Exposition and
                     admonition on not associating with Jews (also called On the Former People of
                     God) (fols. 65vb [incipit]-73rb [explicit])
 I-17) Canons of Simon the
                     Canaanite (n°1) (fols. 84ra-86rb [explicit]), incomplete
 I-18) Letter of
                     Peter to Clement (fols. 86rb [incipit]-87ra [explicit]), incomplete
 I-19)
                     Apostolic Canons: 81 canons (fols. 87ra [incipit]-88vb), incomplete
 I-20)
                     Canons of the Council of Antioch (fols. 92vb [incipit]-97ra [explicit])
                     I-2) Penitential canons given to St Peter (fols. 101vb [incipit]-104vb),
                     incomplete
 
 Additiones 1-3.</summary>
