                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>15th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of Text I and its sections;
                           numbers, titles and incipits of the canons; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1r">f. 1r</locus>
                           <desc>-v: Gadla Samāʿtāt, Vitae of Saints and Martyrs, fragment (incipit
                              page of the Vita of Hernewos).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The leaf originates from the 15th-cent. manuscript AQG-005.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#19r">f. 19r</locus>
                           <desc>-v: Gadla Samāʿtāt, Vitae of Saints and Martyrs, fragment.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The leaf originates from the 15th-cent. manuscript
                           AQG-005. It contains the colophon mentioning 6955 year of mercy (= 1463
                           A.D.) as the date of completion of the writing, and ʾabuna Ṗeṭros as the
                           commissioner. The colophon is preceded by an extensive (historiographic?)
                           note (<locus target="#19r">19r</locus>
                           <note>) mentioning Metropolitan Gabrǝʾel (who arrived in Ethiopia in 1438
                              and died possibly in 1458, s. EAE II, 632). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#106r">f. 106r</locus>
                           <desc>-v: Gadla Samāʿtāt, Vitae of Saints and Martyrs, fragment.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The leaf originates from the 15th-cent. manuscript AQG-005.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Unclear note (possibly a directive for the minister):
                              <locus target="#35v">35v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
